content.description:
SDS at a horizontal and climb a blocky crack system past another horizontal to a somewhat rounded topout.

Listed in the Tram Bouldering Guide as #105, Unnamed.
content.location:
Center of the west face and 5' right of the

Tree Problem

.

content.description:
SDS at a horizontal and climb a blocky crack system to another horizontal (same start as

Warmer-Upper Right

) and then move left on jugs to more jugs over the lip.

This problem isn't listed in the Tram Bouldering Guide but is an obvious line with some good moves that's worth a go when in the area.
content.location:
Center of the west face and 5' right of the

Tree Problem

.

content.description:
Start with hand on holds at the left end of the crack, your feet will be on very small edges.

Make strenuous and increasingly more difficult moves with poor feet until the large jug is gained. From the jug finish straight up.
content.location: Right side of face that you see from the approach path

content.description: SDS at a shelf and power over the bulge on horizontals to a grey knob and then up to the lip.
content.location: Left side of the west face near a small pine tree.

content.description: Start with left and on a poor sloper and right hand on a low side pull.   Pull up onto the rock then make one move to gain the tops holds.
content.location: Located on the left side of the face that you see from the path.

content.description:
SDS with hands matched on a horizontal rail and make a tricky move on thin edges to a juggy finish.

Listed in the Tram Bouldering Guide as #99, Unnamed.
content.location: Left side of the north face.

content.description: Start is to the right of Tree Problem, Obvious chalked ledge, work your way straight up some good holds into a left crimp, pull into the Slumpback and topout from there.
content.protection: crashpad and maybe spotter for topout
content.location: To the right of Tree Problem on the Warmup Boulders S. Face

content.description: SDS way back in an alcove with a wide crack and make a long move to a tramslot then up past horizontals and jugs to the top. Somewhat odd but fun.

Same start as

The Ledge

but traverse left along a sloping rail to a rounded topout. Easier than it looks.

Start the same as

Another Tree Problem

but where that problem heads up keep traversing left along a horizontal to join

The Ledge Traverse

and finish as for that problem. Although somewhat lengthy several sections offer good rests if needed to keep the pump at bay.

content.protection: pad, spotter to keep you off the tree
